article.headline: George Mason 57, Delaware 52
article.story: NEWARK, Del. (AP) -- Will Thomas scored a team-high 14 points and grabbed a game-high 15 rebounds, and George Mason defeated Delaware 57-52 Thursday night. The victory gave Jim Larranaga his 106th CAA win all-time, tying the league record held by Dick Tarrant, formerly of the University of Richmond. Lamar Butler and Folarin Campbell each contributed 10 points for George Mason (16-5, 10-2 Colonial Athletic Association). Harding Nana scored a game-high 16 points and had a team-high 12 rebounds for Delaware (6-14, 2-9).
